column1: Wind Condition: Wind Felt on Face

column2: Overcast- heavy rain within the last 24 hours- wind felt on face- developed shoreline.
Clear skies- wind felt on face- no wildlife.
Overcast weather- heavy fog- light wind. In the past 24 hours there was heavy rainfall. Lake had low boating and fishing traffic. No wildlife observed.
No sighting and purple loostrife at boat landing- clear skies and no wind.
Clear skies.  Moderate wind (Flag extended- leaves move).  Matt Hudson assisted field collection.  Launched at 10:20 am and departed landing at 12:05 pm.
Clear skies.  Slight wind (felt on face).  Jordan Welnetz assisted field collection.  Launched from landing at 10:45 am and departed landing at 12:30 pm.

Clear skies w/  more than 10% scattered clouds.  Very high winds today (small trees swaying). Boat would not stay anchored and we had to move back into place three times.  Jordan Welnetz assisted field collection. Arrived at landing @ 09:45 am and departed at noon.
Arrived at landing at 1245.  Sky had scatterede clouds but sunny.  Slight wind (1).  Departed landing at 1530.
Arrived at landing at 1214.  Sky had broken clouds but sunny.  Heavy wind (4) with difficulty not drifting. Drove back to deep hole spot for some data collection  Departed landing at 1540.
cloudy with se wind cloudy with SE wind
Past 48 Hour Weather: Rain with heavy wind
Past 48 hrs weather- slight rain- wind

column1: Joe Fitzgerald came along to perform plankton sampling
Strange pH reading after 8m- perhaps due to muck on bottom?
Due to motor problems- this was the only site that was measured on Nebagamon on 7/21.

column1: Current weather: partly cloudy- some wind

column1: Current weather: overcast with no wind

column2: Partly cloudy and breezy with a N wind.
Sunny and cold with a light NW wind. Encountered only one other boat on the lake.
It was a beautiful day with no clouds in the sky and a slight breeze out of the NE. Saw no other boats on the lake but saw a Blue Herron fly over.
The day was sunny and mild with a wind out of the NW.

Very windy and unseasonably hot weather. There was no boat traffic on the lake but did see two people swimming. There are not very many years when you can say you went swimming on Sept.15 in northern Wi.
Cool with wind out of the NW.
Muggy- overcast and calm Muggy- overcast and calm. A lot of evergreen tree pollen in the water- makes it hard to tell the difference between algae and pollen.
Muggy- overcast and calm. A lot of evergreen tree pollen in the water.
Partly cloudy with a slight breeze. Saw one adult loon and one juvenile.
Partly sunny with a slight wind. Boat traffic was light.
It was partly sunny and cool with wind out of the north.
Overcast and windy. Overcast and windy
Sunny and a slight breeze. The lake was busy with a lot of boat traffic.
Overcast with light winds. I saw the Great Egret that was reported to me earlier by Hal H.
Sunny with light winds. Saw two people in a paddle boat.

Hazy sunshine with light winds and warm temperatures.  A lot of people removing pontoons and boats for the year. Hazy sunshine with light winds and warm temperatures.  Lake is high because of recent heavy rains. A lot of people are removing boats and pontoons for the season.
Clear and sunny with a light wind out of the NE.
Clear and sunny with a light wind out of the east.  No boat traffic

Partly cloudy and calm.  The lake is still in flood stage (27-30 inches higher) from the Father's Day weekend storms (8-14 inches of rain).  The Lake Association suggested a no wake zone for the entire lake.  A lone paddle boarder kept up with my pontoon while going to the test site.
It rained last night. Clear and sunny with a light north wind. A lot of boat traffic with the boy's club having canoes and sail boats out.
Partly cloudy and calm. Moderate boat traffic.
Clear and calm. Saw one loon and the boat traffic was light.
Calm with hazy sunshine from lifting fog.  No boat traffic. Saw two eagles and heard a loon. Calm with hazy sunshine from lifting fog.  No boat traffic. Saw two eagles and heard a loon.
partly cloudy with a light breeze.
Calm and sunny. There was no boat traffic and my granddaughter Madalyn helped.
Sunny with a light wind and no boat traffic.
Partly cloudy and windy with light boat traffic.
Hot with hazy sun and calm winds. Boat traffic was heavy.
Calm with hazy sun. Haze coming from Canadian wildfires. Boat traffic was light and my wife Renita helped me.
Sunny and calm with moderate boat traffic. Saw 2 rafts of gulls with about 50 birds each. My wife Renita helped again.
Sunny and calm with heavy boat traffic.
Partly cloudy with a light wind. Boat traffic was light.
Partly sunny and cool with a light wind. Boat traffic was light and I saw one loon.
Partly cloudy with a light wind. Boat traffic was moderate and I saw one loon.
Clear and warm with a light wind. Saw 2 boats- 1 jet ski and 4 kayaks.
Warm and sunny with a light wind. Saw 2 fishing boats and one local resident removing a pontoon for the year.
Calm and clear with no boat traffic
Clear and cool with a light wind
Hot- calm- and partly cloudy with moderate boat traffic
Pleasant temperatures with clear skies and light winds. On late July 8 into early July 9 we received 6.7 inches of rain.
Partly cloudy with light winds. Boat traffic was moderate.
Clear skies with light winds. Boat traffic was light.
Partly sunny and calm with heavy boat traffic.
